Settings->2D Viewer

This viewer gives you an "orthographic" camera, that does not show the
perspective view, but a fixed plane view (top, left, front, etc).
This viewer lets you translate the camera in the viewing plane, as
well as roll (rotate along the camera forward direction) and dolly
(move forward/backward).  The popup menu has options to turn grid
on/off, set draw style and so on.  (Click on the "?" button on the
viewer decoration for a Showcase description of a Plane viewer)
